          {
            "id": "body-p1",
            "component": "Text",
            "text": "The streaming docs never say what order a partial surface heals in when updateComponents and updateDataModel land in the same frame. Today the parser flushes components first, so a data-bound child can paint once with a stale value before its model arrives.",
            "as": "p"
          },
          {
            "id": "body-p2",
            "component": "Text",
            "text": "Either the docs should state the guaranteed order, or the parser should flush trailing partials before it closes the surface. Right now an integrator has to read the parser to find out.",
            "as": "p"
          },
